    <h3>Calorie Restriction: The Starvation Response</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Body senses deficit → metabolic rate SLOWS</li>
        <li>Breaks down muscle AND fat equally</li>
        <li>Increases hunger hormones</li>
        <li>Thyroid function decreases</li>
        <li>You feel cold, tired, hungry constantly</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Fasting: The Metabolic Switch</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Body switches fuel sources completely</li>
        <li>Metabolic rate INCREASES (up to 14%)</li>
        <li>Preserves muscle, burns fat preferentially</li>
        <li>Growth hormone surges</li>
        <li>Mental clarity and energy increase</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="key-point">
        <h3>The Banking Analogy</h3>
        <p>Fasting is like switching from your checking account (glucose) to your savings account (fat). Your body has 40,000+ calories stored as fat – it's designed to use them!</p>
    </div>
</section>

