<section id="protocols">
    <h2>Specific Fasting Protocols</h2>

    <p>Different goals require different approaches. Here are the exact protocols used in clinical practice:</p>

    <div class="protocol-box">
        <h4>Beginner Protocol: 12:12</h4>
        <p><strong>Who:</strong> Anyone new to fasting</p>
        <p><strong>How:</strong> 12 hours fasting, 12 hours eating window</p>
        <p><strong>Example:</strong> Stop eating at 7 PM, eat at 7 AM</p>
        <p><strong>Duration:</strong> 2-3 weeks to adapt</p>
    </div>

    <div class="protocol-box">
        <h4>Standard Protocol: 18:6</h4>
        <p><strong>Who:</strong> For weight loss and metabolic health</p>
        <p><strong>How:</strong> 18 hours fasting, 6 hours eating window</p>
        <p><strong>Example:</strong> Eat 12 PM - 6 PM only</p>
        <p><strong>Benefits:</strong> Daily autophagy, steady fat loss</p>
    </div>

    <div class="protocol-box">
        <h4>Advanced: OMAD (One Meal A Day)</h4>
        <p><strong>Who:</strong> Significant weight loss needed</p>
        <p><strong>How:</strong> 23 hours fasting, 1 hour eating</p>
        <p><strong>Frequency:</strong> 3-4 times per week</p>
        <p><strong>Caution:</strong> Ensure adequate nutrition in single meal</p>
    </div>

    <div class="protocol-box">
        <h4>Therapeutic: Extended Fasting</h4>
        <p><strong>36-Hour Fast:</strong> Once monthly for maintenance</p>
        <p><strong>48-Hour Fast:</strong> For breaking weight plateaus</p>
        <p><strong>72+ Hours:</strong> Under medical supervision only</p>
        <p><strong>Who:</strong> Diabetes reversal, severe obesity</p>
    </div>

    <h3>What You Can Have While Fasting</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Water (unlimited)</li>
