<section id="autophagy">
    <h2>Autophagy: Your Cellular Recycling System</h2>

    <p>Autophagy literally means "self-eating" – your cells break down damaged components and rebuild themselves.</p>

    <h3>What Gets Recycled</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Damaged mitochondria (energy factories)</li>
        <li>Misfolded proteins</li>
        <li>Cellular debris</li>
        <li>Pathogens and toxins</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Stem Cell Activation</h3>
    <p>When you break your fast, stem cells surge from bone marrow:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Repair blood vessel damage</li>
        <li>Become immune cells (boost immunity)</li>
        <li>Replace damaged tissues</li>
        <li>Rejuvenate organs</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="protocol-box">
        <h4>Exercise Timing for Maximum Benefit</h4>
        <p><strong>When:</strong> Exercise at the END of your fast</p>
        <p><strong>Example:</strong> Breaking fast at 6 PM? Exercise at 4 PM</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> Growth hormone is highest</p>
        <p><strong>Type:</strong> Resistance training or HIIT</p>
        <p><strong>Result:</strong> More muscle gain, better fat loss</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="women">
    <h2>Women and Fasting: Special Considerations</h2>

    <p>Women can absolutely benefit from fasting, but there are important considerations:</p>

    <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>Do NOT Fast If:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Trying to conceive</li>
            <li>Pregnant or breastfeeding</li>
            <li>History of eating disorders</li>
            <li>Severe adrenal fatigue</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>Female-Specific Modifications</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Start slower:</strong> 12:12 for 4 weeks before progressing</li>
